# gpg

Generate a key
$ gpg --expert --gen-key

Generate a revocation certificate and write it to a file
$ gpg --gen-revoke <key> > rev-certificate.asc

Edit a key
$ gpg --edit-key <key>

Delete secret key
$ gpg --delete-secret-key <key>

Export a backup of the secret keys
$ gpg --export-secret-key <key> > secret.pgp

Import secret keys from a backup
$ gpg --import << secret.pgp

Export the public key
$ gpg --armor --export <key> > public.asc

List public keys
$ gpg -k

List private keys
$ gpg -K
